ugh, but other than that it was really easy.  Pull with lvl 16 Shock of Flame, sic pet on it as it flies in, and watch it pummel itself to death on dmg shield.  Envision a person beating himself silly by bashing his head repeatdly against a wall, and you get the idea...<br>
<br>
One bonus to camping these guys is that it's a great place to work on your defense and dodge skills, if you've let them fall behind (as I have).  The needlites hit fast and soft, so you can take quite a few hits before having to back off.  Usually on the last couple of pulls per spawn I would tank, and gain 1-4 defense or dodge increases.  It's a great thing to do, since most other mobs of this lvl hit so hard that it's tough to tank for long periods.<br>
<br>
The loot is pretty good.  Wings and legs drop fairly often and sell for 2pp 3gp (for a gnome with low cha).  I made 60+ pp in about 1-1/2 hrs and got 3-1/2 yellow bubbles of xp in that time (lvl 30).  This is a great place to go if you can't find a good group elsewhere, or you just like to solo... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Plisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 6:36:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Echo Caverns... great place to lvl and make money!</span><hr size=1> For selling up I've found if you exit the caves to shadowhaven, there is a barbarian trader one door down who seems to offer me better prices than most Shadowhaven and Bazaar merchants.<br>
